{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/blog/my-second-blog/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"name":"Changi Im","title":"Hi, I'm Changi","description":"Electronics Engineering Student in South Korea","about":"Welcome to Changi website!\n    I'm an enthusiastic and challenging engineer student in Korea. I'm always self-motivated and seeking how to live better life.\n    Currently, I'm working at Vision & Imaging Lab in Kyungpook National University and interested in image quality enhancement method via synthesizing those different types of information, such as visible - infrared images, overexposed - underexposed images, or multi-modal image sets. Of course, I have a mind to investigate more various fields in image processing / computer vision, such as object detection, super resolution, or computer graphics something like that.\n    I like to sharing ideas with people, like brainstorming. It is really fun to throw and catch any thoughts so that developing to fancy idea.\n    Anyways, thanks to visit my website again! Belows are more information about me.","author":"","contact":"mailto:imchmcgi250@gmail.com","github":"https://www.github.com/Changi-Im","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/changi-im-aa312a215/"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"5487fbdb-bf06-5457-b1bb-c317a5e2d9db","excerpt":"This post is about my “Smart Pet Robot” project. I did this project with friends for a contest called hanium in korea. We initially made “Smart Robot” as shown…","html":"<p>This post is about my “Smart Pet Robot” project. I did this project with friends for a contest called hanium in korea. We initially made “Smart Robot” as shown below. </p>\n<center>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 347px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 129.05405405405406%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"prototype\" title=\"prototype\" src=\"/static/effd4fab03b37cbcee11191f00da0f4a/4d0aa/prototype.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/effd4fab03b37cbcee11191f00da0f4a/a80bd/prototype.jpg 148w,\n/static/effd4fab03b37cbcee11191f00da0f4a/1c91a/prototype.jpg 295w,\n/static/effd4fab03b37cbcee11191f00da0f4a/4d0aa/prototype.jpg 347w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</center>\nShe is cute right? \nHowever, me and my friends thought she needed an upgrade because she looks a little creepy.&#x1F600; So we came up with a new face for her and the picture below is her new design. \n<center>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 81.75675675675677%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"design\" title=\"design\" src=\"/static/237b4c1e38389343fdc69f7f95753414/1c72d/design.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/237b4c1e38389343fdc69f7f95753414/a80bd/design.jpg 148w,\n/static/237b4c1e38389343fdc69f7f95753414/1c91a/design.jpg 295w,\n/static/237b4c1e38389343fdc69f7f95753414/1c72d/design.jpg 590w,\n/static/237b4c1e38389343fdc69f7f95753414/307d7/design.jpg 760w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 576px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 78.37837837837837%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"design1\" title=\"design1\" src=\"/static/e3bee5cf3d5f790071de9c7dfd2a3529/ac097/design1.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/e3bee5cf3d5f790071de9c7dfd2a3529/a80bd/design1.jpg 148w,\n/static/e3bee5cf3d5f790071de9c7dfd2a3529/1c91a/design1.jpg 295w,\n/static/e3bee5cf3d5f790071de9c7dfd2a3529/ac097/design1.jpg 576w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</center>\nYea, this is better. \nWe will make her face with LCD display different to previous version. It could make our &quot;Smart Pet&quot;  less creepy than before. I think you guys have heard about &quot;uncanny valley&quot;. The uncanny valley is a hypothesized relation between an object&apos;s degree of resemblance to a human being and the emotional response to the object. <cite><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uncanny_valley\">Wikipedia</a></cite> Right, the last version of our &quot;Smart Pet&quot; is kind of uncanny valley. Me and my friend had felt something strange emotions with her like always.  \n<center>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 77.02702702702703%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"design1\" title=\"design1\" src=\"/static/11d5df9673eb07afd601d775f5a22216/1c72d/Uncanny_Valley.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/11d5df9673eb07afd601d775f5a22216/a80bd/Uncanny_Valley.jpg 148w,\n/static/11d5df9673eb07afd601d775f5a22216/1c91a/Uncanny_Valley.jpg 295w,\n/static/11d5df9673eb07afd601d775f5a22216/1c72d/Uncanny_Valley.jpg 590w,\n/static/11d5df9673eb07afd601d775f5a22216/b040c/Uncanny_Valley.jpg 844w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</center>  \n<p>Nevertheless, as we design her face with LCD, we don’t feel strange emotions anymore. So, yea, Let’s begin to make it!<br>\nFirst, we need a raspberry pi and a display for raspberry pi. I used 3.5 inch LCD display. Once those two materials were prepared, you could use a display on your raspberry pi using the code below.  </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"xml\"><pre class=\"language-xml\"><code class=\"language-xml\">sudo rm -rf LCD-show\ngit clone https://github.com/goodtft/LCD-show.git\nchmod -R 755 LCD-show\ncd LCD-show/\nsudo ./LCD35-show</code></pre></div>\n<p>Second, we need a robot expression video. I was able to find it on youtube like this:<cite><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S79FH99aQWk\">Robot Expressions</a></cite></p>\n<p>The robot expression video was cut with blinking, smiling, and heart eyes. Under the normal state, it provides the blinking video, when the robot detects smile of user, it provides the smiling and heart eyes videos.  </p>\n<center>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"blink_Moment\" title=\"blink_Moment\" src=\"/static/13b4978d98b307d4b4060f8264ccbacf/1c72d/blink_Moment.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/13b4978d98b307d4b4060f8264ccbacf/a80bd/blink_Moment.jpg 148w,\n/static/13b4978d98b307d4b4060f8264ccbacf/1c91a/blink_Moment.jpg 295w,\n/static/13b4978d98b307d4b4060f8264ccbacf/1c72d/blink_Moment.jpg 590w,\n/static/13b4978d98b307d4b4060f8264ccbacf/a8a14/blink_Moment.jpg 885w,\n/static/13b4978d98b307d4b4060f8264ccbacf/6a068/blink_Moment.jpg 960w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"smile_Moment\" title=\"smile_Moment\" src=\"/static/365ee2d30692f0b2003a2f2ae4d4eeca/1c72d/smile_Moment.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/365ee2d30692f0b2003a2f2ae4d4eeca/a80bd/smile_Moment.jpg 148w,\n/static/365ee2d30692f0b2003a2f2ae4d4eeca/1c91a/smile_Moment.jpg 295w,\n/static/365ee2d30692f0b2003a2f2ae4d4eeca/1c72d/smile_Moment.jpg 590w,\n/static/365ee2d30692f0b2003a2f2ae4d4eeca/a8a14/smile_Moment.jpg 885w,\n/static/365ee2d30692f0b2003a2f2ae4d4eeca/6a068/smile_Moment.jpg 960w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; margin: 0 0 30px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"heart_Moment\" title=\"heart_Moment\" src=\"/static/beaecfd5cd7aba3a0dc8896eec748824/1c72d/heart_Moment.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/beaecfd5cd7aba3a0dc8896eec748824/a80bd/heart_Moment.jpg 148w,\n/static/beaecfd5cd7aba3a0dc8896eec748824/1c91a/heart_Moment.jpg 295w,\n/static/beaecfd5cd7aba3a0dc8896eec748824/1c72d/heart_Moment.jpg 590w,\n/static/beaecfd5cd7aba3a0dc8896eec748824/a8a14/heart_Moment.jpg 885w,\n/static/beaecfd5cd7aba3a0dc8896eec748824/6a068/heart_Moment.jpg 960w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</center>  \n<p>At last, I made python code for displaying the above videos according to each condition.  </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">Vid <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> cv2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>VideoCapture<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'./smart_bot_expression/blink.mp4'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> Vid<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>isOpened<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sx<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> sy<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> sw<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> sh<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> smiles<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n        cv2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rectangle<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>roi_color<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sx<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> sy<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sx <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> sw<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sy <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> sh<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">255</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> flag <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n            Vid <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> cv2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>VideoCapture<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'./smart_bot_expression/smile.mp4'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n            flag <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">elif</span> flag <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n            Vid <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> cv2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>VideoCapture<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'./smart_bot_expression/heart.mp4'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n            flag <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>When the robot detects your smile, it alternates between a smile and a heart face. The below videos are the results what we did!  </p>\n<center>\n    <video width = \"50%\" muted autoplay controls>\n        <source src=\"/b43f85bfc2ef821a0b95b4d0048806c9/test_comp.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\n    </video>\n    <video width = \"50%\" muted autoplay controls>\n        <source src=\"/0a44c08aec4c54b4fc4191cf319f3aec/test_disp.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\n    </video>\n</center>  \n<p>As you can see in the last video, the raspberry pi display shows quite slower speed than the computer monitor. We can improve the speed in the raspberry pi display by reducing color gamut. </p>\n<p>However, we did too many things today.😪\nLet’s continue the above work in the next post!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Smart Pet Robot[1]","date":"September 23, 2022","description":"Robot expression"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/my-second-blog/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/my-first-blog/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hello World!"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/my-third-blog/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Smart Pet Robot[2]"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"]}